WEBVTT

00:02.540 --> 00:03.710
Huck: [ Echoing ]
We've all done bad things.

00:03.710 --> 00:04.920
I need you to
do something for me.

00:04.920 --> 00:06.620
[ Echoing ]
We've all hurt people.

00:06.620 --> 00:07.790
Be my Command again.

00:07.790 --> 00:09.750
Kill Cyrus Beene.

00:10.670 --> 00:13.170
It's what you do next
that matters.

00:13.170 --> 00:15.170
You want to kill
Cyrus Beene?

00:15.170 --> 00:18.120
I want you to handle Cyrus,
yes.

00:18.120 --> 00:19.580
[ Scoffs ]
I would do it myself,

00:19.580 --> 00:21.250
but we both know
that's not a possibility.

00:21.250 --> 00:23.290
Mellie, I'm not --
We have no choice.

00:23.290 --> 00:25.540
[ Whispering ]
You're not a killer, Mellie.

00:25.540 --> 00:27.920
I am the Commander in Chief
of the Armed Forces.

00:27.920 --> 00:29.210
I kill every day.

00:29.210 --> 00:30.540
With drones
in far-off villages,

00:30.540 --> 00:32.040
with the choices
I make about

00:32.040 --> 00:33.830
how many troops to send
to keep the peace,

00:33.830 --> 00:35.670
which countries get aid
from my government.

00:35.670 --> 00:39.580
People die on my watch
every day.

00:39.580 --> 00:44.540
All of them more innocent
than Cyrus Rutherford Beene.

00:44.540 --> 00:46.080
You're under suspicion
for attempted murder

00:46.080 --> 00:47.290
for taking
Cyrus' plane down.

00:47.290 --> 00:48.960
What do you think happens
when you're --

00:48.960 --> 00:53.290
You are as precise
and capable a killer as any,

00:53.290 --> 00:56.880
and do you know you can make
Cyrus' death look --

00:56.880 --> 00:59.540
I do not kill!

00:59.540 --> 01:01.460
[ Sighs ]
Not anymore.

01:01.460 --> 01:05.670
♪♪

01:05.670 --> 01:08.540
418,000 Americans
died in World War II.

01:08.540 --> 01:09.670
♪♪

01:09.670 --> 01:11.580
Heroes.

01:11.580 --> 01:13.580
There is such a thing
as a just war.

01:13.580 --> 01:15.330
And we are
in the middle of one.

01:15.330 --> 01:17.120
This is not a war.

01:17.120 --> 01:18.580
This is war!

01:18.580 --> 01:20.830
And he is the architect
of this war.

01:20.830 --> 01:22.880
He is the villain, Olivia.

01:22.880 --> 01:24.250
Where is your patriotism?

01:25.830 --> 01:27.210
I am the state.

01:27.210 --> 01:30.170
He is the enemy
of the state.

01:30.170 --> 01:31.960
He is attacking democracy,

01:31.960 --> 01:33.120
attacking the Oval,
attacking freedom.

01:33.120 --> 01:34.540
Attacking you.

01:34.540 --> 01:37.500
Attacking me.

01:37.500 --> 01:39.380
Me, Liv.

01:39.380 --> 01:41.250
♪♪

01:41.250 --> 01:43.880
You worked so hard
to get me here.

01:43.880 --> 01:48.460
Two women outran the boys

01:48.460 --> 01:51.330
all the way to the Oval.

01:51.330 --> 01:56.710
Cyrus doesn't get to steal that
out from under us.

01:56.710 --> 02:01.620
Cyrus does not get to rewrite
the history of women.

02:01.620 --> 02:06.460
He doesn't get
to erase our climb.

02:06.460 --> 02:07.710
Does he?

02:07.710 --> 02:13.710
♪♪

02:16.710 --> 02:18.790
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

02:18.790 --> 02:20.500
Cyrus:
Admiral, thanks for coming.

02:20.500 --> 02:21.750
I just want to make sure

02:21.750 --> 02:23.290
we're keeping an eye
on Mellie.

02:23.290 --> 02:24.250
Things are ramping up.

02:24.250 --> 02:25.460
We need to be sure

02:25.460 --> 02:26.880
she's not gonna try to do
anything stupid.

02:26.880 --> 02:28.710
Of course.

02:28.710 --> 02:29.960
But I also think
we might consider
adjusting the plan.

02:29.960 --> 02:31.500
Adjusting the plan?

02:31.500 --> 02:32.960
[ Chuckles ]

02:32.960 --> 02:35.170
Now is not the time
to start --
Well, hear me out.

02:35.170 --> 02:36.540
You said yourself
that Olivia Pope

02:36.540 --> 02:38.620
isn't going to sit quietly by
and let this happen.

02:38.620 --> 02:40.830
Olivia Pope.
I think
the timing's right

02:40.830 --> 02:42.420
for a targeted,
preemptive strike

02:42.420 --> 02:43.960
against Olivia Pope
and her team.

02:43.960 --> 02:45.000
If we can just --

02:45.000 --> 02:46.750
Don't be greedy, admiral.

02:46.750 --> 02:52.080
We have the chessboard set up
exactly the way we want it.

02:52.080 --> 02:53.380
The queen is in check.

02:53.380 --> 02:54.620
Impeachment is nigh.

02:54.620 --> 02:56.960
Now is not the time
to go on the offensive.

02:56.960 --> 02:59.920
We do that, we risk making
ourselves vulnerable.

02:59.920 --> 03:02.460
No, now is the time
to defend our position.

03:02.460 --> 03:04.210
Mr. Vice President,
I'm simply suggesting that --

03:04.210 --> 03:06.000
And I appreciate
the input.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.920
But let's not
overcomplicate things, huh?

03:07.920 --> 03:09.380
Stick to my plan.

03:09.380 --> 03:11.460
[ Chuckling ] The President
of the United States

03:11.460 --> 03:13.330
is a prisoner
in her own house.

03:13.330 --> 03:14.920
You just need to make sure

03:14.920 --> 03:16.500
she stays that way,
all right?

03:16.500 --> 03:18.080
♪♪

03:18.080 --> 03:19.080
Yes, sir.

03:19.080 --> 03:20.330
Attaboy.

03:20.330 --> 03:22.920
♪♪

03:22.920 --> 03:24.330
The British PM,

03:24.330 --> 03:25.380
the Prime Ministers of India,
Pakistan,

03:25.380 --> 03:27.420
the President of France,
the German Chancellor --

03:27.420 --> 03:29.250
Just tell me
who hasn't called.

03:29.250 --> 03:30.420
Um, I don't know
if there --

03:30.420 --> 03:31.420
Who -- who --

03:31.420 --> 03:33.710
Who should
I get on the line first?

03:33.710 --> 03:36.040
No one.
No one?

03:36.040 --> 03:37.250
But they will call.
They will all call.

03:37.250 --> 03:38.710
I will need to tell them
something!

03:38.710 --> 03:40.830
First of all,
wipe that look off your face.

03:40.830 --> 03:42.210
You are a woman.
Not Bambi.

03:42.210 --> 03:43.880
And this is the White House,
not a blazing forest.

03:43.880 --> 03:45.120
Yes, ma'am.

03:45.120 --> 03:48.880
[ Sighs ]

03:48.880 --> 03:50.620
"The President
is very busy doing her job

03:50.620 --> 03:51.880
for the American people.

03:51.880 --> 03:53.620
She will return your call
when she is able."

03:53.620 --> 03:55.710
That is what
you will tell them.
Yes, ma'am.

03:55.710 --> 03:57.380
Because until
further notice,

03:57.380 --> 03:59.460
the only person
you put through to me

03:59.460 --> 04:01.380
is Olivia Pope.

04:01.380 --> 04:02.420
Yes, ma'am.

04:02.420 --> 04:03.580
♪♪

04:03.580 --> 04:05.330
Tell Secret Service
I'll be using the tunnel

04:05.330 --> 04:06.960
to move between the Oval
and the residence from now on.

04:06.960 --> 04:09.420
♪♪

04:09.420 --> 04:11.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

04:11.000 --> 04:14.170
[ All reporters shouting ]

04:14.170 --> 04:17.420
The Justice Department cannot,
at this time, provide details

04:17.420 --> 04:19.830
without compromising
our ongoing investigation

04:19.830 --> 04:21.830
into the hijacking
of Air Force Two.

04:21.830 --> 04:23.000
What I can confirm

04:23.000 --> 04:24.460
is that President Mellie Grant

04:24.460 --> 04:26.000
is a person of interest
in that investigation.

04:26.000 --> 04:28.040
[ All reporters shouting ]

04:28.040 --> 04:30.290
We will provide updates

04:30.290 --> 04:32.290
as new information
comes to light.

04:32.290 --> 04:33.710
And that is all I can say
at this time.

04:33.710 --> 04:34.960
Thank you.

04:34.960 --> 04:36.170
Man:
Is it true there's a ransom?

04:36.170 --> 04:37.790
You want us to kidnap

04:37.790 --> 04:39.420
the Vice President
of the United States?

04:39.420 --> 04:41.500
No, I just want
access to him.

04:41.500 --> 04:43.580
If I can get him alone,

04:43.580 --> 04:44.790
I can convince Cyrus

04:44.790 --> 04:47.330
to end this ridiculous scheme
against Mellie.

04:47.330 --> 04:51.290
But you're the last person
he wants to see right now.

04:51.290 --> 04:52.500
Do you still have
the number he gave you?

04:52.500 --> 04:53.540
Yeah, but it was a burner.

04:53.540 --> 04:55.120
He must have gotten rid of it
by now.

04:55.120 --> 04:56.790
Obviously, but if I can
figure out his movements

04:56.790 --> 04:58.290
while he had it on him --
Olivia: It might give us
a location

04:58.290 --> 04:59.250
for this little
heart-to-heart.

04:59.250 --> 05:00.830
Do it.

05:00.830 --> 05:02.620
We'll need a copy
of his schedule to
cross-reference.

05:02.620 --> 05:04.330
David can help
on that front.

05:04.330 --> 05:05.250
Huck: And if you can't
talk Cyrus out of it,

05:05.250 --> 05:06.380
what then?

05:06.380 --> 05:07.460
♪♪

05:07.460 --> 05:09.250
Is there a Plan "B"?

05:09.250 --> 05:10.920
Quinn: We're Plan "B."

05:10.920 --> 05:12.960
While Liv's appealing
to Cyrus' better angels,

05:12.960 --> 05:14.670
we'll be searching his phone
for proof

05:14.670 --> 05:16.750
that he coordinated the attack
on his own plane.

05:16.750 --> 05:18.380
If we can find
the hacker he used,

05:18.380 --> 05:20.080
we can take Cyrus down
and clear Charlie's name.

05:20.080 --> 05:24.250
♪♪

05:24.250 --> 05:25.710
How is everything fine?

05:25.710 --> 05:27.880
Your boss
is being accused of treason.

05:27.880 --> 05:29.420
I've heard.

05:29.420 --> 05:31.210
Are you caught up
in this?

05:31.210 --> 05:33.880
Are you gonna be fired
or arrested?
No.

05:33.880 --> 05:35.210
Well, what about me?

05:35.210 --> 05:36.330
After the --
After the business with Robert?

05:36.330 --> 05:37.920
You have nothing to worry about,
Nessa.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.000
How can you be so calm?

05:39.000 --> 05:40.580
Because I know
I'm safe.

05:40.580 --> 05:41.830
Because I know
we're safe.

05:41.830 --> 05:43.460
The Vice President and I

05:43.460 --> 05:45.580
happen to have a very solid
working relationship,

05:45.580 --> 05:47.620
and he has assured me
that once the dust settles,

05:47.620 --> 05:49.960
I will have a central role
in his administration.

05:49.960 --> 05:51.460
Everything I'm doing
is for the two of us.

05:51.460 --> 05:52.880
We're gonna be okay.

05:52.880 --> 05:54.250
Trust me.

05:59.880 --> 06:01.620
You promise?

06:01.620 --> 06:03.920
[ Chuckles ]
Absolutely.

06:03.920 --> 06:05.330
We're a team.

06:11.750 --> 06:13.330
The president's
approval ratings.

06:13.330 --> 06:15.460
These are the most recent
numbers?
Yes, sir.

06:15.460 --> 06:18.000
They've -- Well,
they've gone down a lot.

06:18.000 --> 06:19.540
One subpoena, and they're
already crucifying her?

06:19.540 --> 06:20.790
Sad.

06:20.790 --> 06:21.880
Oh, and more of these.

06:21.880 --> 06:23.290
I know
you don't like these.

06:23.290 --> 06:25.170
You throw them away
every time you get them.

06:25.170 --> 06:27.540
But they must be in season
or something.

06:27.540 --> 06:28.710
No, um...

06:28.710 --> 06:31.330
They're...lovely.

06:31.330 --> 06:32.500
[ Sighs ]

06:37.540 --> 06:39.670
Sir, if the president
gets impeached,

06:39.670 --> 06:40.710
that means...

06:40.710 --> 06:41.960
It means that you...

06:41.960 --> 06:44.210
Yes, Hannah.

06:44.210 --> 06:46.040
But for
President Grant's sake,

06:46.040 --> 06:47.880
let's hope
it doesn't come to that.

06:50.420 --> 06:51.880
[ Door closes ]

06:55.580 --> 07:01.500
♪♪

07:01.500 --> 07:07.500
♪♪

07:07.830 --> 07:09.620
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

07:09.620 --> 07:13.170
♪♪

07:13.170 --> 07:14.880
Lonnie,
we're gonna have --

07:14.880 --> 07:17.120
[ Cork pops ]
Olivia: Lonnie couldn't
make it today.

07:17.120 --> 07:19.080
You'll have to settle
for me instead.

07:19.080 --> 07:20.710
Take a seat, Cyrus.

07:20.710 --> 07:23.080
♪♪

07:27.830 --> 07:29.380
Carol, I didn't say that.

07:29.380 --> 07:30.620
So, then, President Grant
is being considered

07:30.620 --> 07:32.170
a suspect for what happened
on Air Force Two?

07:32.170 --> 07:33.670
Just say no, Audrey.
Just say no.

07:33.670 --> 07:36.170
I-I can't speak for
the Justice Department or --

07:36.170 --> 07:37.960
Man: Then who can you
speak for, Audrey,

07:37.960 --> 07:39.460
because we're not getting
any answers here.

07:39.460 --> 07:40.790
I already said

07:40.790 --> 07:42.580
that I'd be glad to find out
the nature of --

07:42.580 --> 07:43.830
Of how to punt
our questions better?

07:43.830 --> 07:46.330
I'm doing everything I can
to answer your questions

07:46.330 --> 07:48.330
with the information
I have available right now.

07:48.330 --> 07:49.040
[ TV shuts off ]
Why are you even up there?

07:52.170 --> 07:53.500
Marcus.

07:53.500 --> 07:54.920
Madam President.

07:54.920 --> 08:00.960
♪♪

08:03.710 --> 08:09.710
♪♪

08:12.170 --> 08:14.670
[ Sighs ]

08:14.670 --> 08:16.750
How are you holding up?

08:16.750 --> 08:17.920
[ Sighs ]

08:17.920 --> 08:19.460
Jake Ballard is using
my own press secretary

08:19.460 --> 08:20.460
against me.

08:20.460 --> 08:21.710
I've been better.

08:21.710 --> 08:23.080
You're being framed.

08:23.080 --> 08:26.330
I'm being royally f--
framed.

08:26.330 --> 08:27.790
That's why I'm here.

08:27.790 --> 08:29.380
[ Sighs ]
I'm glad you're here,

08:29.380 --> 08:31.120
but there's --
To help fight back.

08:31.120 --> 08:33.250
Cyrus is controlling
the narrative right now.

08:33.250 --> 08:35.040
You need to be
out there in the press

08:35.040 --> 08:36.580
denying these allegations.

08:36.580 --> 08:40.080
The groundskeepers
planted peonies.

08:42.710 --> 08:45.000
Since when do you care about
some damn flowers?

08:47.120 --> 08:49.500
I'm not usually
into flowers.

08:49.500 --> 08:51.080
But lately,

08:51.080 --> 08:52.710
this is the only spot
where I can get some peace.

08:52.710 --> 08:55.000
This isn't over.

08:55.000 --> 08:56.750
There's only one way
it's over.

08:56.750 --> 08:58.040
One way this ends.
What's that?

08:58.880 --> 09:00.620
Don't worry.

09:00.620 --> 09:02.380
I worry when people
tell me not to.

09:02.380 --> 09:04.210
[ Sighs ]

09:07.290 --> 09:10.540
The Chrysanthemums
were hard to keep alive,

09:10.540 --> 09:13.830
so they're trying
the peonies.

09:13.830 --> 09:16.500
I'm not allowed
to see things die.

09:16.500 --> 09:18.460
I'm protected.

09:21.120 --> 09:23.830
[ Whispering ] Olivia is
working on something for me.

09:23.830 --> 09:27.080
[ Whispering ]
What do you mean
by "something"?

09:27.080 --> 09:29.290
This office gets you
one way or the other.

09:29.290 --> 09:31.420
It got Fitz.
It got me.

09:31.420 --> 09:33.290
Either you let someone
take it from you,

09:33.290 --> 09:35.170
or you lose yourself
fighting back.

09:35.170 --> 09:36.790
What are you
talking about?

09:36.790 --> 09:38.210
[ Sighs ]

09:38.210 --> 09:40.540
Mellie,
if you think for once...

09:40.540 --> 09:42.670
[ Normal voice ] Thank you
for stopping by, Marcus.

09:42.670 --> 09:44.330
Rachel?

09:44.330 --> 09:45.580
Rachel: Yes?
[ Normal voice]
What are you doing, Mel?

09:45.580 --> 09:48.500
Can you show Mr. Walker out,
please?

09:48.500 --> 09:50.330
♪♪

09:50.330 --> 09:51.580
Everything's gonna be okay.

09:51.580 --> 09:54.080
♪♪

09:54.080 --> 09:55.960
[ Door opens, creaks ]

09:55.960 --> 10:01.960
♪♪

10:03.790 --> 10:05.290
[ Door closes ]

10:05.290 --> 10:11.290
♪♪

10:11.670 --> 10:17.670
♪♪

10:17.750 --> 10:20.080
[ Sighs heavily ]

10:20.080 --> 10:22.380
Olivia:
I would have much preferred
for all this to go down

10:22.380 --> 10:23.960
on the steps
of the Lincoln Memorial.

10:23.960 --> 10:26.040
You and me, late at night,

10:26.040 --> 10:28.080
talking about our hopes,
our fears,

10:28.080 --> 10:29.830
our wants, and our needs.

10:29.830 --> 10:31.710
Just like the old days.

10:31.710 --> 10:33.750
What are you doing,
Liv?
But, man.

10:33.750 --> 10:35.500
Times sure have changed.

10:35.500 --> 10:37.170
Haven't they, Cy?

10:39.250 --> 10:41.210
Hm.

10:41.210 --> 10:43.080
First,
I'm gonna take your phone.

10:43.080 --> 10:44.380
Huck, take his phone.

10:46.420 --> 10:47.580
You're gonna want
to give it --
Okay.

10:50.210 --> 10:51.420
I'll be right outside.

10:52.420 --> 10:53.920
[ Keypad beeps ]

10:53.920 --> 10:55.120
[ Lock disengages ]

10:57.330 --> 10:58.960
Next I'm gonna make you
an offer.

11:00.460 --> 11:03.580
End this. Now.

11:03.580 --> 11:06.460
Call your boy
and convince him to drop

11:06.460 --> 11:08.750
this outrageous investigation
into the president.

11:08.750 --> 11:10.960
You do that,
you prove to me you still have

11:10.960 --> 11:12.750
some semblance of good
left in you,

11:12.750 --> 11:15.540
somewhere, buried deep,
I'm sure,

11:15.540 --> 11:16.960
then I'll have no choice
but to let you go.

11:16.960 --> 11:19.120
[ Chuckles ]

11:19.120 --> 11:21.210
Appreciate the offer, Liv.

11:21.210 --> 11:23.380
Very much.

11:23.380 --> 11:25.040
But I'm afraid
I'm gonna have to reject it.

11:25.040 --> 11:27.830
So, what's the alternative?

11:27.830 --> 11:28.920
The alternative?

11:28.920 --> 11:30.500
That's what I said.

11:30.500 --> 11:32.170
[ Chuckles ]

11:36.080 --> 11:40.710
♪♪

11:40.710 --> 11:42.960
There are people
outside this room right now

11:42.960 --> 11:45.460
piecing together the details,

11:45.460 --> 11:48.330
figuring out exactly how
you hijacked that plane

11:48.330 --> 11:51.040
and exactly
who you paid to do it.

11:51.040 --> 11:52.460
Huck already has your phone,
Cyrus.

11:52.460 --> 11:53.620
My team --

11:53.620 --> 11:55.500
You know who else
is outside this room?

11:55.500 --> 11:56.710
Another team.

11:56.710 --> 11:58.380
A team of this country's
finest Secret Service.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.420
Wondering where the hell
the Vice President

12:00.420 --> 12:02.210
has run off to.

12:02.210 --> 12:04.500
And I'm very sorry, Liv,
but this team -- my team --

12:04.500 --> 12:05.670
whole lot better

12:05.670 --> 12:07.540
than your gaggle
of misguided thugs

12:07.540 --> 12:09.710
and one rather irritating
little ginger.

12:09.710 --> 12:11.500
What do you think's
gonna happen

12:11.500 --> 12:12.710
when someone finds me here

12:12.710 --> 12:14.620
with the president's
former chief of staff?

12:14.620 --> 12:15.580
I'll tell you.

12:15.580 --> 12:16.790
They're gonna say,

12:16.790 --> 12:19.580
"Mellie wasn't satisfied
with attempted murder.

12:19.580 --> 12:22.580
She had to go and add kidnapping
to the list, too?"

12:22.580 --> 12:25.460
So, someone finds you here.

12:25.460 --> 12:26.330
You're right.

12:26.330 --> 12:28.080
That would be
very, very bad.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.960
Indeed.
For you.

12:29.960 --> 12:32.500
You wouldn't want someone
to find you in the same place

12:32.500 --> 12:35.290
you and Lonnie Mencken
hatched your evil plans,

12:35.290 --> 12:36.420
would you?

12:36.420 --> 12:39.710
The world gets wind
of potential collusion

12:39.710 --> 12:42.750
between the Veep
and a special prosecutor?

12:42.750 --> 12:44.460
I don't know.

12:44.460 --> 12:45.830
How do you think
that one plays out?

12:45.830 --> 12:47.920
I think if you had
any proof of said collusion,

12:47.920 --> 12:49.580
then perhaps the Veep
would be worried.

12:49.580 --> 12:50.670
But clearly, you don't,

12:50.670 --> 12:52.670
otherwise you would have
used it by now.

12:52.670 --> 12:54.290
I was able to figure
out how the two of you
were communicating

12:54.290 --> 12:56.420
in less than an hour.

12:56.420 --> 12:58.120
Gerber daisies wouldn't have
been my choice, but --

12:58.120 --> 12:59.540
All you figured out

12:59.540 --> 13:02.040
was how to tangle yourself up
in a situation

13:02.040 --> 13:04.580
you have absolutely no reason
being a part of.

13:04.580 --> 13:06.170
Enough!

13:06.170 --> 13:08.790
Olivia,
this isn't your war to wage.

13:08.790 --> 13:10.000
She fired you.

13:12.380 --> 13:14.000
Do you want to go back
to prison?

13:14.000 --> 13:16.420
Do you miss it that much?

13:16.420 --> 13:17.420
What I miss, Liv,

13:17.420 --> 13:19.000
is this wine.

13:19.000 --> 13:20.500
Haven't had it in ages.

13:21.580 --> 13:22.790
Mmm.

13:22.790 --> 13:24.580
Still never disappoints.

13:24.580 --> 13:25.830
[ Chuckles ]

13:25.830 --> 13:28.080
Then drink up, Cy.

13:28.080 --> 13:30.460
Savor it
while you still can.

13:30.460 --> 13:31.960
♪♪

13:31.960 --> 13:33.460
[ Chuckles ]

13:33.460 --> 13:35.620
Cyrus: Don't mind me.

13:35.620 --> 13:38.540
Just getting comfortable.

13:38.540 --> 13:40.880
Seeing how we may be here
a while.

13:40.880 --> 13:43.880
♪♪

13:43.880 --> 13:44.880
Ah.

13:44.880 --> 13:45.620
♪♪

13:45.620 --> 13:47.290
Cyrus: Ahh.

13:51.960 --> 13:52.710
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

13:52.710 --> 13:54.250
Incoming!

13:54.250 --> 13:55.750
You got that digital clone
of Cyrus' phone?

13:55.750 --> 13:57.620
Huck's transmitting it now.
Is Huck coming back?

13:57.620 --> 13:58.710
That's not for Huck.

13:58.710 --> 14:00.670
What --
You want me to hack?

14:00.670 --> 14:03.210
You're always talking about
how you wanted to learn code.

14:03.210 --> 14:04.790
Yeah, I've also been meaning
to take up tap-dancing,

14:04.790 --> 14:06.540
but not while the fate of
the nation rests on my shuffle.

14:06.540 --> 14:09.040
Abby, if Cyrus has been talking
to some black-hat hacker,

14:09.040 --> 14:10.880
their communications
will be on this phone.

14:10.880 --> 14:12.080
The problem -- our problem --

14:12.080 --> 14:13.580
is that they'll be behind
layers of encryption.

14:13.580 --> 14:14.880
I don't even know
what that means.

14:14.880 --> 14:15.750
It means
I need your help.

14:19.170 --> 14:20.710
[ Clears throat ]
Fine.

14:20.710 --> 14:22.040
Let's do this.

14:22.040 --> 14:23.500
Let's hack this sucker.

14:23.500 --> 14:24.710
Okay.

14:24.710 --> 14:26.540
Cyrus' phone
should be loaded up.

14:26.540 --> 14:28.290
Open it with the emulator.

14:28.290 --> 14:29.710
You know,
the virtual phone thingy.

14:29.710 --> 14:30.710
Oh. I knew that.

14:30.710 --> 14:34.880
♪♪

14:34.880 --> 14:36.880
[ Sighs ] Oh, God.

14:40.170 --> 14:41.540
I'm worried.

14:41.540 --> 14:44.040
About...?
Mellie.

14:44.040 --> 14:45.710
I know her, and the woman
I just left in the Oval

14:45.710 --> 14:46.750
isn't the woman I know.

14:46.750 --> 14:48.210
She's under
tremendous stress.

14:48.210 --> 14:49.380
She's in a prison
over there.

14:49.380 --> 14:50.830
That place is a prison.

14:50.830 --> 14:52.960
Don't just brush it
off like she's having
another bad day.

14:52.960 --> 14:54.210
She's being framed!
Fitz: I know.

14:54.210 --> 14:56.250
It's a coup.
I know.

14:56.250 --> 14:57.290
Then why does it seem like
you don't care?

14:58.620 --> 14:59.920
I care.

14:59.920 --> 15:02.880
She's dark. Desperate.

15:02.880 --> 15:04.170
Capable of going to a place

15:04.170 --> 15:05.830
she won't be able
to come back from.

15:05.830 --> 15:07.040
To the place Liv went.

15:07.040 --> 15:09.040
That office --
It does that to you.

15:10.670 --> 15:12.880
That's your response?

15:12.880 --> 15:14.920
No offense, but --
Oh, I'm sure
I'll be offended.

15:14.920 --> 15:16.460
You wouldn't understand.

15:16.460 --> 15:19.120
Because I've never been
the president?
Yes.

15:19.120 --> 15:21.210
This isn't normal!
She isn't normal!

15:21.210 --> 15:22.790
She isn't right!

15:22.790 --> 15:23.960
Her presidency
is under attack,

15:23.960 --> 15:25.620
as is her legacy.

15:25.620 --> 15:27.000
I've been there.
It's not easy.

15:27.000 --> 15:29.710
And sometimes?

15:29.710 --> 15:31.500
There is only one way out --

15:31.500 --> 15:33.250
a way you never would have
possibly considered,

15:33.250 --> 15:35.620
but now it's the only way.

15:35.620 --> 15:37.620
Mellie knew
what she was signing up for.

15:37.620 --> 15:39.670
That doesn't make it easier,
but she will survive.

15:39.670 --> 15:41.710
Because you did?
What?

15:41.710 --> 15:43.210
She'll survive

15:43.210 --> 15:44.620
whatever dark deed
she's been contemplating

15:44.620 --> 15:45.790
because you did?

15:45.790 --> 15:47.120
Yes.

15:49.000 --> 15:50.000
Did you?

15:50.000 --> 15:51.040
What?

15:51.040 --> 15:53.000
Survive it. The Oval.

15:53.000 --> 15:55.880
Are you past all
the horrible things you did?

15:55.880 --> 15:59.540
The dark, tough choice you made
to protect your legacy?

15:59.540 --> 16:01.040
[ Chuckling ] Because...

16:01.040 --> 16:03.920
[ Chuckles, scoffs ]
What?

16:03.920 --> 16:04.960
Nothing.

16:04.960 --> 16:06.170
Say it.

16:06.170 --> 16:08.000
You could have fooled me.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.750
You seem haunted,
tormented.

16:10.750 --> 16:12.540
And, yeah, you survived.

16:12.540 --> 16:15.540
But don't you think Mellie
deserves better than that?

16:15.540 --> 16:21.580
♪♪

16:21.620 --> 16:27.620
♪♪

16:27.670 --> 16:29.250
Karen recently let it slip
that she's thinking about

16:29.250 --> 16:30.670
breaking up
with her boyfriend.

16:30.670 --> 16:33.500
Neil Fitzpatrick.

16:33.500 --> 16:36.880
My dear Karen.

16:36.880 --> 16:39.710
There have been so many.

16:39.710 --> 16:40.830
I counseled against it,

16:40.830 --> 16:42.380
which, of course,
had the reverse effect.

16:42.380 --> 16:45.750
Anyway,
now that I think about it,

16:45.750 --> 16:48.670
Neil reminds me of you.

16:48.670 --> 16:50.710
[ Chuckles ]

16:50.710 --> 16:52.500
I liked Neil.
Neil was different.

16:52.500 --> 16:53.790
Considerate.

16:53.790 --> 16:55.920
But also
the kind of strong hand

16:55.920 --> 16:57.250
that Karen
needs in her life.

16:57.250 --> 16:58.040
[ Chuckles ]

16:58.040 --> 16:59.290
By all measurements,

16:59.290 --> 17:03.830
Neil Fitzpatrick
was perfect.

17:03.830 --> 17:06.460
Karen claimed
that he was becoming needy,

17:06.460 --> 17:09.330
deeply insecure.

17:09.330 --> 17:11.460
Posing as an equal partner
in public,

17:11.460 --> 17:13.750
but behind closed doors,
looking for a mommy,

17:13.750 --> 17:15.920
a master.

17:15.920 --> 17:17.420
[ Sighs ]

17:17.420 --> 17:19.540
Honestly,
I doubted Karen's every word.

17:19.540 --> 17:21.750
Told her to stick it out.

17:21.750 --> 17:23.580
I mean, how could someone be

17:23.580 --> 17:26.290
so upstanding and strong
one minute,

17:26.290 --> 17:27.880
then so weak and needy
the next?

17:27.880 --> 17:29.670
It's impossible, right?

17:29.670 --> 17:32.540
I was wrong.

17:32.540 --> 17:35.420
Karen was right.

17:35.420 --> 17:39.120
And now I see

17:39.120 --> 17:44.830
you are
my Neil Fitzpatrick.

17:44.830 --> 17:47.460
A delusional,
insecure little boy

17:47.460 --> 17:49.460
who believes he's a leader,

17:49.460 --> 17:51.920
but in truth,
has only ever followed.

17:51.920 --> 17:53.960
One girl to another,

17:53.960 --> 17:56.460
one master to the next.

17:56.460 --> 18:02.040
All the while looking strong
and pretty on the outside.

18:02.040 --> 18:03.750
I see you.

18:03.750 --> 18:06.790
Olivia sees you.

18:06.790 --> 18:08.080
Oh, oh.

18:08.080 --> 18:10.250
[Chuckling] Cyrus sees you.

18:10.250 --> 18:12.580
[ Chuckles ]

18:12.580 --> 18:15.500
Explains why it was so easy
for him to steal you.

18:15.500 --> 18:17.000
Use you.

18:17.000 --> 18:20.000
[ Chuckles scornfully ]

18:20.000 --> 18:24.040
Now see me!

18:24.040 --> 18:25.750
I earned this office.

18:25.750 --> 18:28.120
I am a leader of men.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.750
I will always be
exactly what I am,

18:30.750 --> 18:32.960
and you will always be
exactly what you are --

18:32.960 --> 18:35.540
Neil Fitzpatrick,

18:35.540 --> 18:37.250
without the excuse
of being young.

18:37.250 --> 18:38.580
[ Chuckles ]

18:38.580 --> 18:41.250
And soon enough,
you will be all alone again.

18:41.250 --> 18:43.830
No master. No allies.
No love.

18:43.830 --> 18:47.290
Because...time's up!

18:47.290 --> 18:49.710
We're coming for you.

18:49.710 --> 18:53.620
♪♪

18:53.620 --> 18:56.500
[ Sighs ]

18:56.500 --> 18:58.170
[ Door closes ]

18:59.790 --> 19:01.080
Any word from Quinn?

19:01.080 --> 19:03.040
Cyrus isn't budging?

19:04.830 --> 19:06.000
You'll keep at him.

19:10.330 --> 19:11.830
It's the '76, isn't it?

19:13.750 --> 19:15.500
Can't be the '87.

19:15.500 --> 19:17.000
He's already drinking
one of those.

19:18.710 --> 19:20.330
Is it the '76?

19:20.330 --> 19:21.750
What are you
talking about?

19:21.750 --> 19:23.330
The wine.

19:23.330 --> 19:24.540
The poison.

19:24.540 --> 19:26.120
Plan "B."

19:26.120 --> 19:29.540
You bought three bottles
of Du Bellay.

19:29.540 --> 19:32.000
Two '87s -- your favorite --

19:32.000 --> 19:33.880
and one '76 because you needed
to be able to remember

19:33.880 --> 19:35.080
which one you poisoned.

19:39.120 --> 19:40.790
Huck.

19:40.790 --> 19:43.040
I just got you back.

19:43.040 --> 19:44.960
I haven't
done anything yet.

19:44.960 --> 19:47.750
Yet.

19:54.790 --> 19:56.120
Quinn will track down
the hacker.

19:56.120 --> 19:58.290
We will get Cyrus
to drop this.

19:58.290 --> 20:00.920
Plan "A" will work.

20:10.830 --> 20:11.710
[ Keypad beeps ]

20:16.960 --> 20:18.500
You know what I've been
thinking about a lot lately?

20:18.500 --> 20:19.670
My goddaughter.
Sweet, sweet Ella.

20:19.670 --> 20:20.750
How's she doing
these days?

20:20.750 --> 20:22.420
[ Laughs ]

20:22.420 --> 20:25.210
If you think you can guilt me
into becoming a better person

20:25.210 --> 20:27.040
by bringing up my daughter,
Liv,

20:27.040 --> 20:28.460
it won't work.

20:28.460 --> 20:32.170
Reeks of desperation.
Sad, rookie move.

20:34.120 --> 20:37.750
Want to know who I've been
thinking about lately?

20:37.750 --> 20:41.960
Unless it's whoever you hired
to take down Air Force Two,

20:41.960 --> 20:43.420
I don't particularly
see the point.

20:43.420 --> 20:44.960
Fitz. I think about him.

20:44.960 --> 20:46.040
More than I'd like
to admit sometimes.

20:48.670 --> 20:50.830
It's a shame you haven't been
able to get over him.

20:50.830 --> 20:54.460
I often wonder
if it all comes back to him --

20:54.460 --> 20:56.710
if the two of us are here
in this room right now

20:56.710 --> 20:58.080
all because of Fitz.

20:58.080 --> 20:59.580
He brought us together,
you know.

20:59.580 --> 21:02.080
He made us.

21:02.080 --> 21:03.960
Friends. Once.

21:03.960 --> 21:05.500
Friends forever.

21:05.500 --> 21:08.540
Bound together
by all those secrets.

21:08.540 --> 21:11.120
You ever think
what would have happened

21:11.120 --> 21:14.750
if you never met him?

21:14.750 --> 21:18.960
Where you'd be
in the world?

21:18.960 --> 21:21.500
You think -- You think
you'd be a better person?

21:21.500 --> 21:23.250
Okay, that's offensive.

21:23.250 --> 21:25.080
I'm sorry.

21:25.080 --> 21:26.580
Not better. Different.

21:26.580 --> 21:27.790
Do you think you'd be
a different person?

21:27.790 --> 21:29.250
If I'd never met Fitz?

21:29.250 --> 21:30.000
If you'd never met Fitz.

21:31.920 --> 21:33.620
Come on.

21:33.620 --> 21:34.960
What do you think?

21:34.960 --> 21:36.120
It's just the two of us.

21:41.080 --> 21:43.170
[ Scoffs ]

21:43.170 --> 21:44.790
Whatever it is that
you're up to right now --

21:44.790 --> 21:46.540
It's an honest question.

21:46.540 --> 21:50.080
There's nothing about you
that's honest.

21:50.080 --> 21:51.330
I want to see something.
That's all.

21:51.330 --> 21:52.330
What?

21:52.330 --> 21:53.880
What do you want to see?

21:53.880 --> 21:56.880
Answer the question.
Hmm?

21:56.880 --> 21:58.120
And I'll tell you.

22:00.380 --> 22:05.830
[ Laughing ]

22:05.830 --> 22:09.170
You're ridiculous.
Maybe so.

22:09.170 --> 22:10.750
I'm gonna need another.

22:10.750 --> 22:12.540
Can I get you one?
I'll get it.

22:17.580 --> 22:20.250
I'd be exactly the same.

22:20.250 --> 22:22.290
[ Laughing ] No different.

22:22.290 --> 22:25.250
No change, whatsoever,
and I know that, Liv.

22:25.250 --> 22:27.540
I can answer that question,
Liv,

22:27.540 --> 22:28.830
because I, unlike you,

22:28.830 --> 22:30.920
know exactly
the kind of person I am.

22:30.920 --> 22:33.620
The kind
who'd trade his conscience in

22:33.620 --> 22:35.460
for a shot at power.

22:35.460 --> 22:37.620
Without ever thinking twice.

22:37.620 --> 22:39.250
I know.

22:39.250 --> 22:40.880
If I wasn't keeping
Fitz's secrets,

22:40.880 --> 22:42.250
I'd be keeping
someone else's.

22:42.250 --> 22:44.000
If I wasn't knocking Mellie
from the throne,

22:44.000 --> 22:45.000
I'd be doing it
to someone else.

22:45.000 --> 22:46.170
Doesn't matter.

22:46.170 --> 22:48.670
I am who I am,
and I always will be.

22:48.670 --> 22:51.330
So...

22:51.330 --> 22:53.290
listen to me
when I tell you,

22:53.290 --> 22:55.750
you can't do a damn thing
about it.

22:55.750 --> 23:01.000
♪♪

23:01.000 --> 23:06.170
♪♪

23:06.170 --> 23:08.540
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

23:08.540 --> 23:09.830
♪♪

23:09.830 --> 23:11.040
[ Sighs ]

23:11.040 --> 23:12.960
[ Bottle thuds ]

23:12.960 --> 23:15.500
I think you've had enough
for now.

23:15.500 --> 23:18.830
[ Laughing ]
You're wasting your time, Liv.

23:18.830 --> 23:20.380
We're wasting our time.

23:20.380 --> 23:22.420
You're gonna have
to let me go.

23:22.420 --> 23:23.620
Olivia!

23:23.620 --> 23:25.290
[ Keypad beeps, door opens ]

23:25.290 --> 23:27.790
Let me...!

23:27.790 --> 23:29.710
[ Sighs ] Go.

23:29.710 --> 23:31.380
♪♪

23:31.380 --> 23:32.960
[ Computer pinging ]
Abby: It stopped.

23:32.960 --> 23:34.580
Why did it stop?
Did I do something?

23:34.580 --> 23:35.710
Yeah, you -- you did.

23:35.710 --> 23:37.000
You infected Cyrus' phone

23:37.000 --> 23:38.920
with a virus
that changed his password.

23:38.920 --> 23:40.580
Okay, enter "LS-New."

23:40.580 --> 23:42.170
Hit return.

23:42.170 --> 23:43.080
Tell me the numbers you see.

23:43.080 --> 23:44.620
0522.

23:44.620 --> 23:45.080
[ Gasps ]

23:46.040 --> 23:48.040
We're in!

23:48.040 --> 23:49.210
What do you want --
texts or phone calls?
Okay, no, no, no.

23:49.210 --> 23:50.420
Don't bother.
They'll be clean.

23:50.420 --> 23:52.040
You see
that bright red icon?
Mm-hmm.

23:52.040 --> 23:53.750
That's an end-to-end
encrypted message app.

23:53.750 --> 23:55.670
No back doors.
No zero-day vulnerabilities.

23:55.670 --> 23:57.960
9 out of 10 hackers
recommend it for shady
business dealings.

23:57.960 --> 24:00.120
Oh, like the one
you and Charlie use

24:00.120 --> 24:02.710
when you send stuff
to each other?
Exactly.

24:02.710 --> 24:05.080
Let's see who Cyrus
has been sending stuff to.

24:05.080 --> 24:06.920
LilPymp69?

24:06.920 --> 24:08.580
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

24:08.580 --> 24:10.120
Yes.

24:10.120 --> 24:11.710
That's our hacker.
Now what?

24:11.710 --> 24:12.750
Uh, let's track them down.

24:12.750 --> 24:14.250
Open your TOR browser.

24:14.250 --> 24:15.330
[ Gasps ]
Ooh, the darknet?

24:15.330 --> 24:17.170
I've never been
on the darknet before.

24:17.170 --> 24:18.670
Well,
what are you waiting for?

24:18.670 --> 24:24.670
♪♪

24:27.880 --> 24:29.620
What if --
Quiet.

24:29.620 --> 24:31.580
[ Sighs ]

24:31.580 --> 24:37.580
♪♪

24:37.880 --> 24:43.080
[ Cellphone chiming ]

24:43.080 --> 24:45.880
[ Sighs ]

24:45.880 --> 24:47.920
♪♪

24:47.920 --> 24:49.120
Quinn?

24:49.120 --> 24:50.290
We found the hacker.

24:50.290 --> 24:51.420
And...?

24:51.420 --> 24:52.250
♪♪

24:52.250 --> 24:53.290
He's dead.

24:53.290 --> 24:55.670
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

24:55.670 --> 24:56.670
Cyrus killed him.

24:56.670 --> 24:58.290
My guess --
He'll kill Charlie, too.

24:58.290 --> 25:01.790
♪♪

25:01.790 --> 25:03.290
[ Cellphone beeps ]

25:03.290 --> 25:06.250
♪♪

25:06.250 --> 25:08.670
Uh, we still have
other options.

25:08.670 --> 25:13.830
♪♪

25:13.830 --> 25:15.790
I'm going to head back in.

25:15.790 --> 25:17.080
In 20 minutes,

25:17.080 --> 25:18.750
I'll place an anonymous call
with the Metro Police.

25:18.750 --> 25:19.880
Don't do this.

25:19.880 --> 25:21.960
First responders
will find Cyrus' body

25:21.960 --> 25:25.420
and a bottle of wine
containing cyanide.
[ Sighs ]

25:25.420 --> 25:27.920
All attempts to revive him
will be futile.

25:27.920 --> 25:29.380
All clues will lead to...

25:29.380 --> 25:31.540
Liv, please.
...Lonnie Mencken
as the murderer.

25:31.540 --> 25:33.080
This isn't you.
Justice will be served.

25:33.080 --> 25:35.920
Liv.
Huck.

25:35.920 --> 25:39.670
It's time for you to go.

25:39.670 --> 25:41.710
Please.

25:41.710 --> 25:47.710
♪♪

25:51.380 --> 25:57.380
♪♪

26:06.000 --> 26:07.750
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

26:07.750 --> 26:09.330
Fitz: Mellie?

26:09.330 --> 26:10.420
Hey.

26:10.420 --> 26:11.580
Hi.

26:16.670 --> 26:18.210
How are you?

26:18.210 --> 26:19.670
Me? I'm fine.

26:19.670 --> 26:21.380
How are you?
Fine.

26:21.380 --> 26:23.080
Good.

26:26.330 --> 26:27.420
[ Sighs ]

26:30.080 --> 26:32.170
[ Sighs ]

26:33.380 --> 26:36.330
♪♪

26:36.330 --> 26:37.460
Mellie.

26:37.460 --> 26:39.960
It's lonely here.

26:39.960 --> 26:41.620
I know.

26:41.620 --> 26:43.710
[ Sighs ]

26:43.710 --> 26:45.750
I know you know.

26:45.750 --> 26:47.460
Is there something
I can do?

26:47.460 --> 26:52.620
♪♪

26:52.620 --> 26:57.750
♪♪

26:57.750 --> 26:59.040
You're doing it.

26:59.040 --> 27:00.460
You're talking to me.

27:00.460 --> 27:02.960
♪♪

27:02.960 --> 27:05.290
I really don't have
anyone to talk to.

27:05.290 --> 27:06.710
Even though
I can't really talk.

27:06.710 --> 27:08.750
♪♪

27:08.750 --> 27:10.670
I spoke to Marcus.

27:10.670 --> 27:12.540
♪♪

27:12.540 --> 27:14.880
You don't need it,
but here's some advice.

27:14.880 --> 27:17.790
Find another way,
if you can.

27:17.790 --> 27:19.670
That office
doesn't have to feel to you

27:19.670 --> 27:20.920
the way it did for me.

27:20.920 --> 27:22.790
I went there, Mellie.

27:22.790 --> 27:23.830
I justified it.

27:23.830 --> 27:25.040
People forgave me.

27:25.040 --> 27:26.210
I forgave myself.

27:26.210 --> 27:29.080
But I have never
been the same.

27:31.620 --> 27:34.210
Find another way.

27:34.210 --> 27:35.670
Don't lose it.

27:35.670 --> 27:37.120
Lose what?

27:38.670 --> 27:39.620
Your soul.

27:39.620 --> 27:42.670
♪♪

27:42.670 --> 27:45.330
You're better than me.

27:45.330 --> 27:47.250
You're better
than all of us.

27:47.250 --> 27:49.330
♪♪

27:49.330 --> 27:51.120
Don't forget that.

27:51.120 --> 27:53.460
I should go.

27:53.460 --> 27:55.330
Okay.

27:55.330 --> 27:57.380
Okay.

27:57.380 --> 28:00.460
♪♪

28:00.460 --> 28:01.330
[ Door opens ]

28:02.330 --> 28:03.500
Mr. Mencken.

28:03.500 --> 28:05.000
Admiral,
we have a problem.

28:05.000 --> 28:06.120
We do.
You shouldn't be here.

28:06.120 --> 28:08.880
The two of us
being seen together

28:08.880 --> 28:10.920
only jeopardizes
this investigation

28:10.920 --> 28:13.080
if it hasn't been
jeopardized already.

28:13.080 --> 28:14.170
The vice president's
schedule

28:14.170 --> 28:15.500
says he's
at physical therapy.

28:15.500 --> 28:18.290
Stretching.
That's our problem.

28:18.290 --> 28:21.210
Cyrus doesn't go
to physical therapy.

28:21.210 --> 28:23.380
That's his cover for when
he's meeting with me.

28:23.380 --> 28:27.040
And if you're here,
that means Cyrus is...

28:27.040 --> 28:28.670
That's our problem.

28:30.420 --> 28:33.460
How about we switch
to the '76 Du Bellay?

28:33.460 --> 28:35.960
Cyrus: All the same to me
at this point.

28:35.960 --> 28:40.580
♪♪

28:40.580 --> 28:41.960
What now?

28:41.960 --> 28:43.830
Nothing.

28:43.830 --> 28:45.670
It's...

28:45.670 --> 28:49.790
♪♪

28:49.790 --> 28:51.710
[ Sighs ]

28:54.790 --> 28:57.880
You're thinking about
what I asked earlier --

28:57.880 --> 28:59.080
whether you'd be different.

28:59.080 --> 29:01.790
Of course I'd be different.

29:01.790 --> 29:04.620
It's not even a question.

29:04.620 --> 29:06.120
You -- You --

29:06.120 --> 29:08.960
Yes, you would be
exactly the same.

29:08.960 --> 29:12.330
You're incapable of change.

29:12.330 --> 29:14.290
But that's not something
to be proud of, Cyrus.

29:14.290 --> 29:15.420
That's...

29:15.420 --> 29:17.830
♪♪

29:17.830 --> 29:19.080
...sad.

29:19.080 --> 29:20.290
♪♪

29:20.290 --> 29:22.170
My drink, Liv.

29:22.170 --> 29:23.540
Something needs
to numb the pain

29:23.540 --> 29:24.670
of being stuck down here
with you.
[ Keypad beeps ]

29:24.670 --> 29:25.830
[ Door opens ]

29:25.830 --> 29:26.960
Mr. Vice President.

29:28.000 --> 29:29.580
You ready
to get out of here?

29:29.580 --> 29:32.710
Ballard, thank God.

29:32.710 --> 29:34.620
I told you.

29:34.620 --> 29:37.750
All this would be
a waste of your time.

29:37.750 --> 29:38.790
Where do you think
you're going?

29:38.790 --> 29:41.290
[ Laughing ] What?

29:41.290 --> 29:42.960
Is she serious?

29:42.960 --> 29:44.170
She can't be serious.

29:44.170 --> 29:45.330
I think she's serious.

29:45.330 --> 29:47.620
You're forgetting
your drink.

29:47.620 --> 29:48.620
No more stalling,
Olivia.

29:48.620 --> 29:49.750
You're not gonna
give him that drink.

29:49.750 --> 29:50.620
We both know why.

29:50.620 --> 29:52.460
[ Sighs ]

29:55.420 --> 29:57.210
Here.

29:58.830 --> 29:59.670
Let me save you
the trouble.

30:01.290 --> 30:03.620
Take it. Go ahead.

30:03.620 --> 30:05.580
It'll be faster. Easier.

30:05.580 --> 30:07.290
Messier, sure.

30:07.290 --> 30:09.330
Shooting Cyrus in the face
requires a bit more cleanup

30:09.330 --> 30:10.830
than getting him to drink
a glass of poison,

30:10.830 --> 30:12.880
but you've got people
for that, right?

30:12.880 --> 30:15.250
♪♪

30:15.250 --> 30:16.710
Take the damn gun,
Olivia!

30:16.710 --> 30:19.420
♪♪

30:19.420 --> 30:21.920
Fine.

30:21.920 --> 30:23.790
You can shoot me, too.

30:23.790 --> 30:24.670
It's okay.
Here. I'll help.

30:24.670 --> 30:30.670
♪♪

30:34.250 --> 30:36.880
Ballard, eh...

30:36.880 --> 30:42.880
♪♪

30:42.920 --> 30:45.000
Eh...
[ Exhales sharply ]

30:45.000 --> 30:48.460
♪♪

30:48.460 --> 30:50.290
She's not gonna do it.
She can't.

30:50.290 --> 30:52.120
She's not gonna kill
either one of us.

30:52.120 --> 30:53.880
She's not capable of --
You have no idea
what I'm capable of.

30:53.880 --> 30:55.500
Oh, you talk a big game,
Olivia Pope,

30:55.500 --> 30:56.880
but when push comes to shove,

30:56.880 --> 30:58.790
you actually
don't do anything.

30:58.790 --> 31:00.670
You give orders.

31:00.670 --> 31:01.960
You unleash your dogs.

31:01.960 --> 31:03.290
You huff and you puff

31:03.290 --> 31:05.380
and you work so damn hard
pretending to be evil.

31:05.380 --> 31:08.580
But at the end of the day,
it's not you.

31:08.580 --> 31:10.620
Getting your hands dirty.
Blowing up planes.

31:10.620 --> 31:12.540
Assassinating world leaders.
No.

31:12.540 --> 31:15.210
That's the work you leave
for people like me.

31:15.210 --> 31:18.420
You, Mellie,
you get to stay clean

31:18.420 --> 31:21.420
because you have
people like me.

31:21.420 --> 31:23.330
You get to lull yourself
to sleep at night

31:23.330 --> 31:25.420
because you have
people like me.

31:25.420 --> 31:27.000
And if you don't
understand that --

31:27.000 --> 31:28.750
If you can't bring yourself
to believe that,

31:28.750 --> 31:30.290
then take the damn gun,
Olivia.

31:30.290 --> 31:31.710
Take it and prove me wrong.

31:31.710 --> 31:37.710
♪♪

31:39.380 --> 31:41.580
Mr. Vice President.

31:41.580 --> 31:47.580
♪♪

31:47.830 --> 31:53.830
♪♪

31:59.460 --> 32:00.830
Jake: Just because
the vice president's safe

32:00.830 --> 32:02.120
doesn't mean we don't have
a problem on our hands.

32:02.120 --> 32:03.290
Well,
it would appear that way,

32:03.290 --> 32:04.250
but if it's all the same
to you,

32:04.250 --> 32:05.790
I prefer
to address this problem

32:05.790 --> 32:07.420
using the instrument
of the law.
I couldn't agree more.

32:07.420 --> 32:08.790
I'd suggest
we widen the investigation

32:08.790 --> 32:10.210
to include Olivia Pope.

32:10.210 --> 32:11.920
I can easily furnish evidence
demonstrating

32:11.920 --> 32:13.880
that she was involved
in Rashad's assassination.

32:13.880 --> 32:14.920
That's all well and good,
admiral,

32:14.920 --> 32:17.290
but if I may be indelicate,

32:17.290 --> 32:18.960
is there a risk
that opening that up

32:18.960 --> 32:20.080
may tarnish other parties?

32:20.080 --> 32:21.290
No, I'd make sure
to scrub anything

32:21.290 --> 32:22.620
pointing
to my own involvement.

32:22.620 --> 32:24.460
But we can review everything
tomorrow morning.

32:24.460 --> 32:26.000
You have a good evening.

32:27.120 --> 32:28.420
So you are involved
in this mess.

32:28.420 --> 32:29.500
Vanessa.

32:29.500 --> 32:31.250
What exactly needs to be
scrubbed, Jake?

32:31.250 --> 32:32.580
Who the hell
were you even talking to?

32:32.580 --> 32:34.330
Go upstairs and go to bed.
And to top it all off,

32:34.330 --> 32:35.790
now you're dragging
Olivia Pope into this?

32:35.790 --> 32:37.420
What the hell is going on?

32:37.420 --> 32:38.830
Look, Olivia Pope can't stay
away from the White House.

32:38.830 --> 32:40.620
She should have been netted
by the special prosecutor

32:40.620 --> 32:41.620
from the start.

32:41.620 --> 32:42.920
All I'm doing --

32:42.920 --> 32:44.620
You promised me that this
was gonna work out for us --

32:44.620 --> 32:45.880
that we were some team.

32:45.880 --> 32:47.250
Vanessa, listen to me.

32:47.250 --> 32:48.500
The lengths
I need to go to right now,

32:48.500 --> 32:50.040
the methods I need to employ,
I just can't --

32:50.040 --> 32:51.290
No, don't you dare
keep telling me

32:51.290 --> 32:52.380
that it's all for us.

32:52.380 --> 32:53.920
It is for us!

32:53.920 --> 32:56.670
You're protecting him,
aren't you?

32:56.670 --> 32:58.380
The vice president.
[ Sighs ]

32:58.380 --> 32:59.920
He's the one that you've
been taking orders from

32:59.920 --> 33:01.920
all this time, isn't he?

33:01.920 --> 33:03.750
What is it that
he's making you do, Jake, huh?

33:03.750 --> 33:05.000
Why don't you tell me?

33:05.000 --> 33:06.750
Is he asking you to get down
on your knees at night,

33:06.750 --> 33:08.920
when you're not here?
Stop talking!

33:08.920 --> 33:10.250
I'm not doing
what the vice president,

33:10.250 --> 33:12.580
or anyone else,
wants me to do.

33:12.580 --> 33:14.880
I'm doing what I think --
what I know is best.

33:14.880 --> 33:17.540
Aligning myself
with the strongest allies

33:17.540 --> 33:19.750
so that we do not get
left behind!

33:19.750 --> 33:21.460
There is no "we."

33:21.460 --> 33:22.540
You really need to watch
where you're going --

33:22.540 --> 33:25.750
I was supposed to be
Jackie Kennedy.

33:25.750 --> 33:27.290
American royalty.

33:27.290 --> 33:30.580
A Daughter of
the American Revolution.

33:30.580 --> 33:32.960
Not the wife of
the vice president's bitch.

33:32.960 --> 33:35.540
♪♪

33:35.540 --> 33:37.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

33:40.670 --> 33:44.290
Olivia:
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:47.670 --> 33:48.710
I couldn't.

33:50.580 --> 33:54.500
It's not who you are,
who we are,

33:54.500 --> 33:57.080
much as I wish it were.

33:57.080 --> 34:01.000
Because now I have
this sick feeling inside me,

34:01.000 --> 34:03.330
like all the water
has drained off the beach,

34:03.330 --> 34:06.880
and we are two fish
flapping on the sand,

34:06.880 --> 34:08.330
eyeing the building tsunami
on the horizon.

34:08.330 --> 34:12.170
We don't need their methods,
their tools.

34:12.170 --> 34:15.830
We don't need to adopt
or justify violence

34:15.830 --> 34:17.460
just because it's been
business as usual

34:17.460 --> 34:18.830
for the men
who have led this country

34:18.830 --> 34:20.670
since its inception.

34:20.670 --> 34:24.500
The sins of our past leaders
don't need to be our sins.

34:24.500 --> 34:27.210
They may always
outnumber us,

34:27.210 --> 34:31.330
out-muscle us,
outgun us.

34:31.330 --> 34:36.960
That is why we need to be
smarter, better...

34:36.960 --> 34:38.540
more just.

34:39.960 --> 34:41.250
The only way
we can win this

34:41.250 --> 34:44.080
is if our bond
is stronger than theirs,

34:44.080 --> 34:50.080
if we hold fast together,
no matter what comes.

34:50.500 --> 34:52.460
Mellie, I am with you.

34:54.460 --> 34:56.710
No matter what you think,

34:56.710 --> 35:01.500
I have always been
with you.

35:01.500 --> 35:03.120
Are you with me?

35:04.880 --> 35:07.710
♪♪

35:07.710 --> 35:10.250
[ Sighs ]

35:10.250 --> 35:11.420
I'm with you.

35:11.420 --> 35:13.670
♪♪

35:13.670 --> 35:15.000
Good.

35:15.000 --> 35:21.000
♪♪

35:23.210 --> 35:25.750
Now what?

35:25.750 --> 35:26.670
[ Sighs ]

35:26.670 --> 35:30.710
♪♪

35:30.710 --> 35:33.460
Now we find a way
to surf the tsunami.

35:33.460 --> 35:38.420
♪♪

35:38.420 --> 35:39.960
Mellie: By now it has been
widely reported

35:39.960 --> 35:42.710
that I have been subpoenaed

35:42.710 --> 35:45.620
in relation to the hijacking
of Air Force Two.

35:45.620 --> 35:47.210
Special Prosecutor
Lonnie Mencken

35:47.210 --> 35:48.750
has referred to me in the press

35:48.750 --> 35:51.620
as a "person of interest"
in the investigation.

35:51.620 --> 35:54.880
Mr. Mencken's comments
have given rise to rumors

35:54.880 --> 35:57.580
that I, myself,
had a vested interest

35:57.580 --> 36:00.380
in the attempted assassination
of Vice President Cyrus Beene.

36:00.380 --> 36:01.580
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
[ All Reporters shouting ]

36:01.580 --> 36:03.330
Madam President.

36:03.330 --> 36:05.540
♪♪

36:05.540 --> 36:07.880
Mellie: That is why
I have come out here tonight.

36:07.880 --> 36:09.250
Woman: Madam President,

36:09.250 --> 36:10.540
are you complicit
with the hijacking?

36:10.540 --> 36:11.750
Is it true you paid a man
named Charlie?

36:13.790 --> 36:15.540
♪♪

36:15.540 --> 36:17.620
[ Sighs ]

36:17.620 --> 36:20.330
♪♪

36:20.330 --> 36:24.420
These rumors,
these allegations,

36:24.420 --> 36:27.880
have been stoked
by my opponents --

36:27.880 --> 36:29.540
opponents who wish
to see the nation

36:29.540 --> 36:31.460
distracted
from the good work

36:31.460 --> 36:34.120
that this administration
has done and continues to do.

36:34.120 --> 36:37.960
Opponents who wish to see me
backed into a corner

36:37.960 --> 36:39.880
and to forever
tarnish my legacy.

36:39.880 --> 36:44.620
To them I say good luck.

36:44.620 --> 36:46.710
Huh.
She didn't kill Cyrus.

36:46.710 --> 36:48.750
♪♪

36:48.750 --> 36:51.040
I will not be backed
into a corner.

36:51.040 --> 36:53.290
I will not allow you
to spread lies

36:53.290 --> 36:54.920
and to call me a terrorist

36:54.920 --> 36:56.580
when I am a patriot.

36:56.580 --> 36:59.580
I'm not trying
to bring down jet planes.

36:59.580 --> 37:04.790
I'm shattering glass ceilings
and making history.

37:04.790 --> 37:09.250
I am keeping our borders safe
and giving our daughters hope.

37:09.250 --> 37:11.290
I am the Commander in Chief.

37:11.290 --> 37:13.880
It is my duty to uphold the law,
not to break it.

37:13.880 --> 37:15.460
I am not guilty.

37:15.460 --> 37:16.960
[ All reporters shouting ]

37:16.960 --> 37:18.420
If you did not
hear me the first time,

37:18.420 --> 37:20.210
let me say it again.

37:20.210 --> 37:25.250
I...am...not...guilty.

37:25.250 --> 37:26.920
♪♪

37:26.920 --> 37:30.750
And I will not be bullied.

37:30.750 --> 37:32.710
♪♪

37:32.710 --> 37:35.210
Truth is on my side,

37:35.210 --> 37:38.830
and I will not stop fighting
until the truth is out.

37:38.830 --> 37:42.540
Thank you.

37:42.540 --> 37:46.500
[ Reporters shouting ]

37:46.500 --> 37:51.210
♪♪

37:51.210 --> 37:53.210
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

37:53.210 --> 37:54.000
[ Knock on door ]

37:55.790 --> 38:01.790
♪♪

38:04.830 --> 38:08.580
I've been thinking.

38:08.580 --> 38:12.880
About the old days, and...

38:12.880 --> 38:15.920
♪♪

38:15.920 --> 38:16.830
...I think that was it.

38:16.830 --> 38:18.250
♪♪

38:18.250 --> 38:19.750
Cask strength.

38:19.750 --> 38:21.580
First fill.

38:21.580 --> 38:24.290
Aged over
an entire 24 years.

38:24.290 --> 38:26.670
It used to be your favorite,
right?

38:26.670 --> 38:28.420
Back in the day?

38:28.420 --> 38:30.290
Your memory serves.

38:30.290 --> 38:35.380
Well, I thought
we could both use a drink.

38:35.380 --> 38:37.040
A drink.

38:37.040 --> 38:40.250
A drink to the old days.

38:40.250 --> 38:42.420
♪♪

38:42.420 --> 38:44.250
To the way
things used to be.

38:44.250 --> 38:50.250
♪♪

38:50.500 --> 38:54.290
You realize that this drink

38:54.290 --> 38:57.880
will require you to share
a very expensive bottle --

39:01.120 --> 39:07.120
♪♪

39:08.620 --> 39:14.620
♪♪

39:17.170 --> 39:19.000
[ Doorbell rings ]

39:20.620 --> 39:21.790
[ Breathing heavily ]

39:21.790 --> 39:22.880
Mr. Vice President.

39:22.880 --> 39:24.250
You're out of breath.

39:24.250 --> 39:26.330
Well, Vanessa and I

39:26.330 --> 39:28.790
are having a bit
of a disagreement.

39:28.790 --> 39:30.120
What are you doing here?

39:34.460 --> 39:36.080
I think maybe
you were right

39:36.080 --> 39:37.880
when you suggested
we find a way

39:37.880 --> 39:39.420
to manage
Liv and her team.

39:39.420 --> 39:42.000
It may be time
to adjust the plan.

39:42.000 --> 39:43.120
I'm happy
to hear you say that.

39:43.120 --> 39:44.750
Things are getting
out of hand.

39:44.750 --> 39:46.540
That speech
Mellie made tonight --

39:46.540 --> 39:48.040
I only hope
we're not too late.

39:48.040 --> 39:49.750
Mr. Vice President,
I've taken care of it.

39:49.750 --> 39:52.380
What did --
t-taken care of it how?

39:52.380 --> 39:53.830
I spoke to Lonnie.

39:53.830 --> 39:55.960
Olivia Pope is now
a person of interest

39:55.960 --> 39:58.040
in both the hijacking
of Air Force Two

39:58.040 --> 39:59.380
and the assassination
of President Rashad.

39:59.380 --> 40:01.250
You called Lonnie?

40:01.250 --> 40:02.460
You can't just --
The ramifications --

40:02.460 --> 40:03.500
Cyrus.

40:04.920 --> 40:07.120
I did not sign off on this.

40:07.120 --> 40:08.960
I didn't need you to.

40:08.960 --> 40:11.170
You didn't need me to?

40:11.170 --> 40:12.710
This is my operation.

40:13.580 --> 40:15.460
[ Snickers ]

40:15.460 --> 40:16.920
Come here.
I want to show you something.

40:16.920 --> 40:22.920
♪♪

40:23.330 --> 40:29.330
♪♪

40:29.750 --> 40:32.210
Ballard,
what did you do?

40:32.210 --> 40:35.000
Mr. Vice President,
when you came to me,

40:35.000 --> 40:37.710
when you asked for my help,
I asked you a question.

40:37.710 --> 40:40.080
Do you remember
what it was?

40:42.380 --> 40:43.380
[ Exhales sharply ]

40:43.380 --> 40:45.880
I asked you

40:45.880 --> 40:47.790
why you thought that
I'd ever work for you.

40:47.790 --> 40:50.000
In response, you claimed that
I wouldn't be working for you.

40:50.000 --> 40:51.790
I'd be working with you.

40:51.790 --> 40:53.830
That it would be you and me
versus the world,

40:53.830 --> 40:55.000
that we'd be a team.

40:55.000 --> 41:00.080
You proposed a partnership.

41:00.080 --> 41:02.330
Vanessa and I
made a similar pact

41:02.330 --> 41:03.540
when we got married.

41:03.540 --> 41:07.000
We agreed to work together,

41:07.000 --> 41:08.120
to have each other's backs,

41:08.120 --> 41:12.290
to listen to one another
as equals.

41:12.290 --> 41:15.330
This evening,
she made it clear that

41:15.330 --> 41:19.500
that arrangement
was no longer acceptable.

41:19.500 --> 41:22.330
It was sadly time
to dissolve our partnership.

41:22.330 --> 41:25.750
♪♪

41:25.750 --> 41:27.580
Yes. I, uh -- I see.

41:27.580 --> 41:30.250
♪♪

41:30.250 --> 41:31.880
I don't work for you,
Cyrus.

41:31.880 --> 41:34.540
I don't need
your permission.

41:34.540 --> 41:35.620
But I am more than happy

41:35.620 --> 41:37.120
to include you
in my decision making,

41:37.120 --> 41:38.580
provided that,
moving forward,

